default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221; gradient_type=&#8221;default&#8221; column_padding_type=&#8221;default&#8221;][vc_column_text]\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>How Immigration Policies Have Changed and What It Means for You<\/strong><\/h2>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]The Labour Government (elected in May 2022) has issued the largest number of invitations for the <strong>Skilled Independent visa (subclass 189) <\/strong>to skilled workers in recent years. The last invitation round in December 2022 is the largest in years and reflects the shift in strategy to run the program, with the government seeking to respond to current skills and labour shortages.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_direction_desktop=&#8221;default&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; desktop_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color=&#8221;#ffffff&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_backdrop_filter=&#8221;none&#8221; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;3px&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; column_position=&#8221;default&#8221; advanced_gradient_angle=&#8221;0&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221; gradient_type=&#8221;default&#8221; column_padding_type=&#8221;default&#8221;][vc_column_text]\n<h3><strong>Recent Skilled Independent Subclass 189 Invitation Rounds<\/strong><\/h3>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]There have been three invitation rounds this program year, totalling a staggering <strong>59,182 invitations<\/strong> issued by the federal government to apply for Subclass 189. This is a positive step forward for the program and represents a significant uplift in invitation numbers compared to previous years, including pre-COVID-19.[\/vc_column_text][divider line_type=&#8221;No Line&#8221; custom_height=&#8221;10&#8243;][image_with_animation image_url=&#8221;110379&#8243; image_size=&#8221;medium_large&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;entrance&#8221; animation=&#8221;None&#8221; animation_movement_type=&#8221;transform_y&#8221; hover_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; alignment=&#8221;center&#8221; border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; box_shadow=&#8221;small_depth&#8221; image_loading=&#8221;default&#8221; max_width=&#8221;100%&#8221; max_width_mobile=&#8221;default&#8221; custom_sizes_attr=&#8221;min-width:400px&#8221;][divider line_type=&#8221;No Line&#8221; custom_height=&#8221;10&#8243;][vc_column_text]\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/immi.homeaffairs.gov.au\/visas\/working-in-australia\/skillselect\/invitation-rounds\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Department of Home Affairs &#8211; SkillSelect invitation Round 2022<\/a> <i class=\"icon-tiny fa fa-external-link\"><\/i><\/p>\n[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_direction_desktop=&#8221;default&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; desktop_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color=&#8221;#ffffff&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_backdrop_filter=&#8221;none&#8221; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;3px&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; column_position=&#8221;default&#8221; advanced_gradient_angle=&#8221;0&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221; gradient_type=&#8221;default&#8221; column_padding_type=&#8221;default&#8221;][vc_column_text]\n<h3><strong>What to expect from the increased number of invitations?<\/strong><\/h3>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]Australia\u2019s strict COVID-19 border closures heavily impacted the Migration program. Still, while Australia has been slow at welcoming skilled migrants back to its shores, the latest invitation rounds suggest <strong>a positive trend<\/strong> in Australian Skilled Immigration policies.<\/p>\n<p>This new approach by the Department may mean that providing you have a score of at least 65 points, an invitation to apply for a visa can be expected by the next invitation round. However, it is worth highlighting that some ANZSCO occupations naturally have more EOIs lodged than others. This means that the number of invitations issued each round may be limited, and not all candidates who complete an EOI will receive an invitation to apply for a visa.<\/p>\n<p>If you are preparing to apply for a\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/skilled-independent-189-visa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Skilled Independent visa (subclass 189)\u00a0visa<\/strong><\/a>,\u00a0you must plan each step carefully. It is a long process to apply for a skilled visa, and steps such as the English test or the Skills Assessment are crucial. It is vital to remember that requirements can and do change, and it is a good idea to keep checking as you go to ensure that you have not been adversely affected by any changes.<\/p>\n<p>We can help you prepare and lodge what could be a life-changing visa application. Our in-depth knowledge of Skilled Independent visa (subclass 189) law and procedures, allows us to help our clients submit a \u201cdecision-ready\u201d application. This is an application that includes all supporting documents and information needed for the processing officer to make a decision at the earliest possible.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#82